Paris Saint-Germain will allow Mbappe join Premier League giants, Liverpool on one condition And this is if the Premier League giants can pay the astonishing price being demanded by PSG. The Athletic reports that the Parisians want to block the player from moving to Real Madrid. However, they are open to allowing the France international to join the Reds. A £352m (€400m) price tag was placed on the 2018 World Cup winner, who was told ‘any exit would have to be to Liverpool’. Mbappe is said to have ‘rejected’ this opportunity. Angelo Henrique, PSG’s technical director, had claimed in August 2022 that Liverpool club could get the player He said the Reds could get the player if they are willing to spend an astonishing transfer fee of €400 million and that offer is now reportedly back on the table.